{
  "text": "Studies have demonstrated the biological and drug response alterations associated with galectin-3 SNPs in cancer [CITATION_1] ; however, only a limited number of studies have investigated the function of galectin-3 rs4644 and rs4652 polymorphisms in the susceptibility and chemotherapeutic drug resistance of GC. Galectin-3 functional genetic variations may contribute to the development and chemotherapy response of GC. The objective of the present study was to evaluate the association between galectin-3 rs4644 and rs4652 genotypes with the risk of developing GC and its chemotherapy drug resistance in a hospital-based case-control study.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "38167017"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "38167017": {
      "title": "Galectin-3 in cancer",
      "abstract": "Galectin-3 (Gal-3) plays important roles in cell proliferation, adhesion, differentiation, angiogenesis and apoptosis in normal and pathologic tissues. Accumulated evidences indicate that Gal-3 is closely involved in tumor cell transformation, migration, invasion and metastasis. In this review, the associations of the expression and localization of Gal-3 as well as its potential action mechanism in tumorigenesis in a variety of cancers were summarized and concluded. Gal-3 is gaining its attraction as a potential new biomarker for the diagnosis, treatment and prognosis of certain tumors."
    }
  }
}